						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Trikūṭēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1184-85 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1107, Krōdhi, the other details being lost. The date corresponds to 1184-85 A.D., the Śaka year being current.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift to the god Trikūṭēśvara. It mentions Ereguppe in Huligeṟe Three Hundred. Mention is also made of Hermāḍirāya, probably of the Chālukya family and Chandrabhūshaṇamuni. The record is fragmentary and damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
